[{"location":"#ArgoData.jl-1","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package is at a very early stage of development. Stay tuned ...","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [MITprof,DownloadArgo]\nOrder   = [:type,:function]","category":"page"},{"location":"#ArgoData.MITprof.loop","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.MITprof.loop","text":"loop(pth::String=\"profiles/\")\n\nStandard Depth Argo Data Collection – see ?MITprof.read for detail.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ArgoData.MITprof.read","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.MITprof.read","text":"read(f::String=\"MITprof/MITprof_mar2016_argo9506.nc\")\n\nStandard Depth Argo Data Example.\n\nHere we read the MITprof standard depth data set from https://doi.org/10.7910/DVN/EE3C40 For more information, please refer to Forget, et al 2015 (http://dx.doi.org/10.5194/gmd-8-3071-2015) The produced figure shows the number of profiles as function of time for a chosen file     and maps out the locations of Argo profiles collected for a chosen year.\n\nusing ArgoData, Plots\n\nfi=\"MITprof/MITprof_mar2016_argo9506.nc\"\n(lo,la,ye)=MITprof.read(fi)\n\nh = histogram(ye,bins=20,label=fi[end-10:end],title=\"Argo profiles\")\n\nye0=2004; ye1=ye0.+1\nkk=findall((ye.>ye0) .* (ye.<ye1))\nscatter(lo[kk],la[kk],label=fi[end-10:end],title=\"Argo profiles count\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.GDAC_FTP-Tuple{String,Int64,Int64}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.GDAC_FTP","text":"GDAC_FTP(b::String,y::Int,m::Int)\n\nDownload Argo data files for one regional domain (b), year (y), and month (m) from the GDAC FTP server (ftp://ftp.ifremer.fr/ifremer/argo or, equivalently, ftp://usgodae.org/pub/outgoing/argo).\n\nb=\"atlantic\"; yy=2009:2009; mm=8:12;\nfor y=yy, m=mm;\n    println(\"$b/$y/$m\"); DownloadArgo.GDAC_FTP(b,y,m)\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.GetOneProfile-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.GetOneProfile","text":"GetOneProfile(m)\n\nGet one profile from netcdf file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.mitprof_interp_setup-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.mitprof_interp_setup","text":"mitprof_interp_setup(fil::String)\n\nGet parameters etc from yaml file (fil).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_PtoZ!-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_PtoZ!","text":"prof_PtoZ!(prof,meta)\n\nConvert prof[\"p\"] to prof[\"depth\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_TtoΘ!-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_TtoΘ!","text":"prof_TtoΘ!(prof,meta)\n\nConvert prof[\"T\"] to potential temperature\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_interp!-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.prof_interp!","text":"prof_interp!(prof,meta)\n\nInterpolate from prof[\"depth\"] to meta[\"z_std\"]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_adtg-Tuple{Any,Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_adtg","text":"sw_adtg(S,T,P)\n\nCalculate adiabatic temperature gradient as per UNESCO 1983 routines from salinity (S; in psu), in situ temperature (T; in °C), and pressure (P; in decibar)\n\nadtg = sw_adtg(S,T,P)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_dpth-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_dpth","text":"sw_dpth(P,LAT)\n\nCalculate depth in meters from pressure (P; in decibars) and latitude (LAT; in °N)\n\nd = sw_dpth(100.0,20.0)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_ptmp","page":"Home","title":"ArgoData.DownloadArgo.sw_ptmp","text":"sw_ptmp(S,T,P,PR)\n\nCalculate potential temperature as per UNESCO 1983 report from salinity (S; in psu), in situ temperature (T; in °C), and pressure (P; in decibar) relative to PR (in decibar; 0 by default).\n\nptmp = sw_ptmp(S,T,P,PR=missing)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
